'''Anders Johan Sjögren''', also spelled '''Andreas Johan Sjögren''', May 8, 1794 in [[Iitti]], [[Finland]] – January 18, 1855 in [[St. Petersburg]], [[Russia]]) was a [[Finland|Finnish]] linguist, ethnographer, historian and explorer. He is known e.g. as the person who discovered the [[Vepsian people|Veps people]].

